<section xml:id="sec_egspace_summ">
  <title>Summary</title>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <p>
        An eigenspace of an <m>n \times n</m> matrix <m>A</m> corresponding to an eigenvalue <m>\lambda</m> of <m>A</m> is the null space of <m>A - \lambda I_n</m>.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        To find a basis for an eigenspace of a matrix <m>A</m> corresponding to an eigenvalue <m>\lambda</m>,
        we row reduce <m>A - \lambda I_n</m> and find a basis for <m>\Nul A - \lambda I_n</m>.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        Eigenvectors corresponding to different eigenvalues are always linearly independent.
      </p>
    </li>
  </ul>
</section>